title: Keen: Next Error
content:
Hey everyone, I'm new [img]http://www.classicgaming.com/cc314/msgboard/emotikeen-grin.gif[/img]
EDIT: OOPS! I meant to comment in the editor thread! Sorry! Not a good way to start a new account, eh?
Anyways,
I'm having an error, too.
Whenever I try to "Create Keen Files" (or whatever it is underneath the 'File' menu button) and I click on keen4e.exe, a box comes up telling me, "Couldn't determine exe version number." so I press ok, and then another box comes up telling me, "Couldn't extract maphead." Then it just goes back to what it looks like when you first open Keen: Next editor.
These are legitimate keen games, too, installed right off the floppy. Am I missing something?

Looks great, though, I hope I can get it working.

title: Re: Keen: Next Error
content:
You haven't unlz'd your executable; that is, it is still compressed.

You need to download unlzexe.exe and drag the Keen4e.exe file onto it. This will create a keen4e.old file and your execuatable will decompress [become larger] This is also vital if you are using ck4patch, which you will have to if you want to actually play the new levelsA proud member of the Spleen Extinction society
